+{"id":"franken_numpy-1vlq","title":"conformance_ma.rs harness for numpy.ma mask semantics","description":"Add a standalone fnp-python integration conformance harness for the numpy.ma surface. The README advertises masked arrays as a supported API family, but crates/fnp-python/tests currently has no conformance_ma.rs family harness even though other families have dedicated differential matrices. The harness should compare fnp_python.ma against numpy.ma for mask propagation, masked reductions, weighted average returned tuples, masked ediff1d boundary insertion, construction/all-mask behavior, and error surfaces. Acceptance: cargo test -p fnp-python --test conformance_ma passes under rch and emits a family summary; the committed test file should be self-contained enough for future agents to extend with additional numpy.ma parity cases.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:02:38.908018781Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:06:55.358972647Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T20:06:55.357035051Z","close_reason":"Added crates/fnp-python/tests/conformance_ma.rs, a standalone numpy.ma integration harness. The harness compares fnp_python.ma with numpy.ma for construction/all-mask behavior, masked_where, filled, masked_invalid, native count/average/ediff1d wrappers, and invalid-axis error alignment. Verified with rch cargo test -p fnp-python --test conformance_ma (6/6 MUST + 3/3 SHOULD pass), rch cargo check --workspace --all-targets, rch cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings, cargo fmt --check, and UBS on the changed test file.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-1w2y","title":"numpy.linalg.eig python wrapper parity","description":"Add fnp_python.eig passthrough wrapper around numpy.linalg.eig(a). Returns (eigenvalues, right_eigenvectors) for general (non-symmetric) matrices. Include oracle test covering: 2x2 diagonal matrix → exact eigenvalues, 3x3 general matrix matching numpy values up to permutation, complex eigenvalues for rotation-like matrix, batched 3-D input, singular matrix returning correct results, and verify A@v ≈ λ*v reconstruction.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T11:52:47.066659707Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T10:41:54.464006467Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T10:41:54.461759919Z","close_reason":"Closed by cc-numpy — wrapper + oracle parity test delivered in commit 1dbdc09 (verified via git log --grep br-franken_numpy-1w2y).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-1xwh","title":"Match NumPy FFT Inf-component propagation","description":"The FFT adversarial harness shows Rust FFT outputs all NaN for input [1, Inf, 3, -Inf], while NumPy preserves infinite imaginary components for some coefficients. Investigate twiddle handling/special values and match NumPy's non-finite component behavior without regressing NaN propagation.","notes":"Fixed FFT Inf-component propagation to match NumPy. Added fft_mul() helper that treats near-zero twiddle factors (|x|<1e-14) as exactly zero when multiplied with Inf/NaN. All 1975 fnp-ufunc tests pass.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T12:08:39.451158855Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T12:22:56.111223792Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T12:22:56.109447970Z","close_reason":"Completed by e9674ff: FFT Inf-component propagation now matches NumPy","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","fft","parity"]}
